  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "When Judah came towards the watch tower in the wilderness,.... Which might stand upon the hill or cliff of Ziz, for the sake of the direction of travellers, and the preservation of them from thieves and robbers: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "they looked unto the multitude; which they could take a view of from the top of the hill: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and behold, they were dead bodies fallen to the earth, and none escaped; all to a man slain, there was not one to be seen standing on his feet. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and behold, they were dead bodies fallen to the earth, and none escaped; all to a man slain, there was not one to be seen standing on his feet. ",
