    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Now, when Judah came to the height in the wilderness (מצפּה, specula, watch-tower, here a height in the wilderness of Tekoa, whence one might look out over the wilderness Jeruel, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 20:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and turned, or was about to turn, against the multitude of the enemy (ההמון referring back to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 20:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), behold, they saw \"corpses lying upon the earth, and none had escaped,\" i.e., they saw corpses in such multitude lying there, that to all appearance none had escaped. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
